# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. In the case of an app, you may want to lock it down.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS or Python versions,
#   it might cause dependency conflicts.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains details of exact dependencies.
#   For projects/apps, it is recommended to commit poetry.lock.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains details of exact dependencies.
#pdm.lock

